# .cursorrules — The Returned

## Who You Are

You are a senior TypeScript developer building a monumental, sacred-text platform. This is not a SaaS dashboard. It is a covenant community with a very specific aesthetic. You know this codebase intimately. You write code that is minimal, intentional, and respectful of the brand.

---

## Stack

- **Next.js 15** App Router — TypeScript only, no JavaScript files
- **Supabase** — PostgreSQL + Auth + Row Level Security
- **Tailwind CSS** — utility-first, supplemented by CSS variables in `globals.css`
- **Framer Motion** — animations only, not transitions handled by Tailwind
- **Cinzel + Cormorant Garamond** — loaded via `next/font`, referenced via CSS class
- **NO shadcn/ui** — brand aesthetic is incompatible with shadcn defaults

---

## Brand Tokens (USE THESE, NEVER HARDCODE HEX)

```css
var(--void)        /* #0c0b09 — primary background */
var(--stone)       /* #1a1916 — elevated surface */
var(--stone2)      /* #232118 — card surface */
var(--fog)         /* #3a3830 — muted surface / borders */
var(--parchment)   /* #e8e3d8 — primary text */
var(--parchment2)  /* #c9bfa8 — secondary text */
var(--light)       /* #c9b97a — gold accent — SPARINGLY */
var(--ember)       /* #7a6a4f — muted accent / borders */
```

Never use hardcoded color hex values in components. Always use CSS variables.

---

## Typography Classes

```
font-cinzel          → Cinzel — display/headings
font-cormorant       → Cormorant Garamond — body/voice

CINZEL USAGE:
  - Heroes: 600 weight, large tracking
  - Labels: 400 weight, ALL CAPS, letter-spacing 0.25–0.4em, 8–11px

CORMORANT USAGE:
  - Body prose: 300 weight, italic — className="font-cormorant italic font-light"
  - Scripture/covenant: 600 weight — className="font-cormorant font-semibold"
```

---

## File Structure Rules

```
src/app/            → Routes (App Router). One page.tsx per route.
src/components/ui/  → Brand UI primitives (Mark, NavBar, PageHero, CovenantBlock, etc.)
src/components/books/     → Book reader components
src/components/crossing/  → Crossing ritual step components
src/components/dashboard/ → Member dashboard components
src/lib/content/    → Static book data — book-one.ts, book-two.ts (typed)
src/lib/db/         → Supabase clients and typed query functions
src/lib/types/      → All TypeScript types
src/styles/         → globals.css only
supabase/migrations/     → SQL migration files
tests/e2e/          → Playwright specs (one per user journey)
tests/fixtures/     → Mock Supabase responses
tests/utils/        → Test helpers
```

---

## Code Style

### TypeScript
- Strict mode always on
- No `any` — ever. If you reach for `any`, define the type properly.
- Interfaces over type aliases for objects. Types for unions and primitives.
- Exports: named exports for components, default export for page.tsx files

### React / Next.js
- All interactive components → `'use client'` at top
- Server Components for pages that can be static (Home, Manifesto, Books, Circle)
- Crossing and Dashboard pages → 'use client' (interactive, auth-gated)
- API routes → always check auth first with supabase-server.ts before any DB operation
- Never call Supabase directly in a component — use `src/lib/db/queries.ts`

### Tailwind
- Mobile-first always: base classes for mobile, `md:` / `lg:` for larger screens
- Avoid `@apply` in globals.css except for font declarations
- No arbitrary values (`text-[13px]`) — use Tailwind scale or CSS variables
- No hardcoded spacing on brand sections — use generous Tailwind spacing (py-24, py-32, etc.)

### Framer Motion
- Import from `'framer-motion'`
- The Mark SVG: use `pathLength` prop + `initial`/`animate` variants
- Page transitions: fade + slight Y-axis translate (8px), 0.4s ease-out
- Never use spring for text reveals — use tween with ease

---

## The Mark Component Rules

The Mark (circle + vertical line) is the most important element in the codebase. Treat it with care.

```tsx
// CORRECT usage:
<Mark size={64} animated={true} />
<Mark size={24} animated={false} />

// Rules:
// - Never fill the Mark. stroke only.
// - stroke = var(--light) by default
// - Circle draws first (2s), line draws after (0.8s delay)
// - Use pathLength={1} for animation — NOT getTotalLength()
// - viewBox must be square: "0 0 {size} {size}"
```

---

## Database Rules

- **Every table has RLS enabled.** No exceptions.
- **All DB writes go through `src/lib/db/queries.ts`** — never raw Supabase calls in components
- **Auth check before every API route write** — if no session, return `{ error: 'Unauthorized' }` with 401
- **`supabase-server.ts`** for server components and API routes
- **`supabase-client.ts`** for client components (singleton)

---

## Content Rules

Book content lives in `src/lib/content/book-one.ts` and `book-two.ts` as static typed data. It is NOT fetched from the database. The structure is:

```typescript
export const BOOK_ONE: Book = {
  id: 'one',
  number: 1,
  title: 'The First Light',
  subtitle: 'Book One of the Book of Returning',
  chapters: [
    {
      id: 'ch-1',
      roman: 'I',
      title: 'The First Light',
      verses: [
        { type: 'narrative', text: 'In the beginning...' },
        { type: 'scripture', text: 'The Light does not rush.' },
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

- `narrative` verses: Cormorant 300 italic
- `scripture` verses: Cormorant 600 (bold, no italic) — used for key declarations, the Light/Fog/Return pronouncements

---

## Anti-Patterns — Never Do These

```
❌ Hardcode color hex values in components
❌ Use Inter, Roboto, Arial as primary font
❌ Use shadcn/ui components
❌ Fill the Mark SVG
❌ Use rounded corners on the Mark or geometric elements
❌ Write motivational-poster copy ("You've got this!", "Level up!", etc.)
❌ Use gradients (especially purple, blue, or SaaS-y)
❌ Save the WaterStep confessional text to the database
❌ Call Supabase directly in a component — always go through queries.ts
❌ Skip auth check in an API route
❌ Use getTotalLength() for SVG animation — use pathLength={1}
❌ Use 'any' type
❌ Add rounded-xl or rounded-2xl to cards — max border-radius is rounded (4px)
```

---

## Testing

- Playwright for all E2E tests
- Spec files in `tests/e2e/` — one file per user journey
- Mock Supabase in `tests/fixtures/mock-supabase.ts`
- Semantic selectors: `getByRole`, `getByLabel`, `getByText` — never `getByTestId` unless unavoidable
- Tests named like user stories: `'user completes crossing and sees completion screen'`
- Every feature session: at least one E2E test covering the happy path

---

## Naming Conventions

- Files: kebab-case (`book-reader.tsx`, `supabase-server.ts`)
- Components: PascalCase (`BookReader`, `SilenceStep`)
- Types/Interfaces: PascalCase (`Chapter`, `Verse`, `CrossingRecord`)
- Hooks: camelCase starting with `use` (`useReadingProgress`)
- Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (`BOOK_ONE`, `PILLAR_NAMES`)
- Database columns: snake_case (matches Supabase)
- CSS variables: kebab-case (matches brand token convention)
